Ingredients.3: 1 (12 ounce) package frozen chopped spinach, thawed and drained

Ingredients.7: 1 salt and ground black pepper to taste

Directions.1: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).

Directions.2: Line two 9-inch pie plates with crusts. Cover crusts with a double layer of aluminum foil and a layer of pie weights or dried beans.

Directions.3: Bake in the preheated oven until edge of crust is golden, about 10 minutes. Carefully remove the foil and weights; continue baking until the crust sets, about 5 minutes more. Let crusts cool briefly. Reduce oven temperature to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).

Directions.4: Sprinkle cheese, spinach, and onion evenly onto the crusts. Whisk eggs, milk, salt, and pepper together and divide evenly between the crusts.

Directions.5: Bake in the center of the preheated oven until golden brown and firm in the centers, about 45 minutes.
